---
description: Do not disable TypeScript checking with ts-nocheck
alwaysApply: true
---

# No `// @ts-nocheck`

- Do not add `// @ts-nocheck` to new or existing files.
- Fix TypeScript errors with proper types, narrower interfaces, `unknown` handling, or focused `@ts-expect-error` comments when an exception is truly unavoidable.
- If an existing file already has `// @ts-nocheck`, do not copy that pattern into new code. Remove it from files you materially rewrite when practical.
